      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Show reminder URLs in Reminders notes",
        "body": "Closes #59.\n\nKeeps `--url` writing the existing EventKit URL field by default and adds explicit `--show-url-in-notes` handling for users who want a Reminders.app-visible managed notes line. The opt-in path writes `remindctl URL (managed): ...` on add/edit, replaces that managed line when the URL changes, removes only that managed line with `--clear-url`, and preserves authored `URL: ...` or plain `remindctl URL: ...` notes.\n\nValidated with `make check`. Live EventKit proof on macOS 27.0 (26A5368g) with Reminders full access: default `add --url` retained the URL field while leaving notes exactly as authored; opt-in `add --url --show-url-in-notes` created the managed notes line, opt-in edit replaced it, and opt-in `--clear-url` removed the URL field and managed line while leaving authored notes as `Codex proof notes`; both disposable proof reminders were deleted.\n",
        "branch": "fix-reminder-url-field",
